&lt;p&gt;The Account Executive is a part of Cleo’s first-class Sales Team and becomes a product knowledge expert while focusing on selling directly to new and current clients, building pipelines, and identifying key client needs to drive sales growth. You’ll leverage AI-powered sales tools and ecosystem insights to prioritize your pipeline, personalize outreach, and close deals faster. We are looking for candidates eager to drive their business, set ambitious goals, and speak fluently about how AI and automation are reshaping supply chain and B2B integration. Cleo is a growing Ecosystem — we want the best and brightest on our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Will Be Doing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Educate and advise clients to build strong, trustworthy relationships with Cleo customers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute a successful sales process from lead to appointment to close&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Obtain feedback from clients and adjust messaging to improve downstream execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meet clients to discuss their needs and complete the execution of the sale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with SDRs and Account Managers to devise a program that meets client needs and budget&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Negotiate with clients, solve problems, and make sure deadlines are met&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check and report on client Cleo program progress&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use AI-driven analytics and intent data to identify high-propensity accounts and prioritize outreach efforts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage Cleo’s AI-powered platform insights to tailor solution narratives that resonate with each prospect’s specific supply chain and integration challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with internal teams to surface AI-generated signals that help anticipate client needs and accelerate deal progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Your Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prior experience in an SDR, BDR, or inside sales role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must have EDI experience in the B2B SaaS industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be willing to travel 30–40% on average&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Display a strong interest in outside sales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate confidently in person, over the phone, and online&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Focus on the positive and strive for continual improvement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be ambitious and motivated to achieve results&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate and operate well in a fast-paced, team-oriented environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to a strong work ethic and sense of commitment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enjoy learning about the IT industry&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with AI-assisted sales tools (e.g., Gong, Clari, Salesforce Einstein, or similar) to manage pipeline health and forecast accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort using AI tools for research, prospecting, and communication to maximize efficiency and output&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Curiosity about how AI and automation are reshaping supply chain, EDI, and B2B integration — and the ability to speak to those trends confidently with prospects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;A Few Things We Have to Offer&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$90,000 to $120,000 Base Salary + commission opportunity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great Healthcare + Dental + Vision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible PTO&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Culture of support, encouraging Life-Work balance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;401k match&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;FSA and HSA options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Parental Leave&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Representing a company with 4,000+ clients and a 99% retention rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Accelerated title and salary growth potential&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fun and energetic work environment that makes you excited to go to work every day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to cutting-edge AI sales enablemen

&lt;h2&gt;About the Role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an experienced AI Product Manager who is passionate about building intelligent products customers love. You will join a dynamic, fast-paced environment and work with cross-functional teams — engineering, data science, design, and go-to-market — to design, build, and launch AI-powered products that deliver our company&#39;s vision and strategy. This role sits at the intersection of applied AI/ML, customer outcomes, and business strategy: you&#39;ll define what we build, why we build it, and how we measure success in a rapidly evolving AI landscape.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You Will Be Doing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the AI product roadmap — including LLM-powered features, predictive models, agentic workflows, and ML-driven automation — translating customer needs into a prioritized, outcome-driven plan.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a deep understanding of customer experience, identify product gaps where AI can deliver disproportionate value, and generate new ideas that grow market share, improve customer experience, and drive growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with data scientists, ML engineers, and software engineers to scope models, evaluate tradeoffs between accuracy, latency, cost, and UX, and ship with quick time-to-market and optimal resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate product strategy into detailed requirements and prototypes, including user stories, MVP scope, acceptance criteria, model evaluation criteria, and KPI frameworks tied to measurable customer outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and monitor AI feature success metrics — including model performance (precision, recall, accuracy), user adoption, and business impact — through dashboards and regular reporting to executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct structured buy / build / partner analysis for new AI capabilities, including evaluation of foundation model providers, third-party AI vendors, and open-source alternatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scope and prioritize activities based on business and customer impact, balancing near-term wins with longer-horizon AI investments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive product launches in collaboration with marketing, PR, executives, and other PM team members — including positioning AI capabilities clearly and avoiding overpromising.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate promotional plans to ensure messaging accurately conveys AI capabilities and limitations, and is consistent with the broader product line strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as an AI product evangelist — both internally and externally — to build awareness, understanding, and trust in our AI capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the company by visiting customers to solicit feedback on AI features, observe real-world use, and surface opportunities for the next wave of intelligent product capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Your Qualifications&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Required&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BS/MS degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Data Science, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3–5 years of proven product management experience, with at least 1–2 years owning AI/ML-powered product features in a SaaS environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of managing all aspects of a successful product throughout its lifecycle — from discovery through launch and iteration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to develop product and AI strategies and effectively communicate recommendations to executive leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid technical background with hands-on understanding of software development, modern AI/ML technologies (LLMs, embeddings, classical ML), and SaaS architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret ML model outputs, understand evaluation metrics (precision/recall, AUROC, RMSE, F1, eval sets for LLMs), and hold technical teams accountable to model quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt

